<L>__{interior guards' barracks evening}
<A>__{a guard slowly turns the dial of a radio, finding and losing in static several different voices in several languages, none of them lasting more than a moment. depression hangs over the barracks. most of the guards are straining to hear the news they've been fearing for some time now, some on their bunks just staring, one at a window peering out at the black face of a forest as if expecting, at any moment, to see russian or american troops appear.}
